43
00:02:54,290 --> 00:02:58,040
Its value with leverage at 20% leverage ratio

44
00:02:58,040 --> 00:03:03,650
is then given by VL equals VU plus PVTS,

45
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:08,270
and that equals 5.66 plus 0.3--

46
00:03:08,270 --> 00:03:09,410
again, the tax rate--

47
00:03:09,410 --> 00:03:14,180
times 0.05, the interest rate, times 0.2, the debt ratio,

48
00:03:14,180 --> 00:03:16,160
times 5.66--

49
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:18,560
the asset value without leverage--

50
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:23,290
and then discounted by 0.1856.

51
00:03:23,290 --> 00:03:28,150
That gives us $5.75 million.

52
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:31,680
Therefore, by using the debt capacity of the asset,

53
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:34,140
